HIV/Aids: China ta sanar da karuwar sabbin masu cutar da kashi 14%
Kasar Sin ta sanar da karuwar mutanenta da ke dauke da cutar HIV da AIDS da kashi 14 cikin dari.
Jami'an kiwon lafiya sun ce fiye da mutane 820,000 a kasar suna fama da cutar.
An gano kimanin sabbin maganganu 40,000 a cikin kwata na biyu na 2018 kadai.
Yawancin lokuta an haife su ta hanyar jinsi, suna nuna canji a baya.
A al'adance, cutar HIV ta yadu cikin sauri a wasu sassan kasar Sin sakamakon samun jinin da aka samu daga masu cutar.
Amma adadin mutanen da suka kamu da cutar ta HIV ya ragu zuwa kusan babu, in ji jami'an kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin a wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
Amma a shekara guda, adadin mutanen da ke cikin kasar Sin da ke dauke da cutar kanjamau ya karu da mutum 100,000.
Cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce a cikin al'ummar LGBT na kasar Sin.
An cire tsarin gay daga tsarin a 1997, amma ana zargin cewa nuna bambanci ga LGBT yana da kyau.
Saboda dabi'un kiyayewa na ƙasar, bincike ya nuna cewa kashi 70% zuwa 90% na maza da suke yin jima'i da maza a ƙarshe suna auren mata.
Yawancin cututtukan cututtuka na cututtuka sun haifar da rashin lafiya a cikin waɗannan dangantaka.
Tun 2003, gwamnatin China ta yi alkawarin samar da magani ga kowa a kasar Sin a matsayin wani bangare na shirin magance cutar.
