Gwamnatin tarayya masu gabatar da kara kira ga m hukunci ga mutumin da ake zargi da kai hari a New York City
Masu gabatar da kara na tarayya a New York suna neman hukunci mafi tsanani ga Sayfullo Saipov, wanda ake zargi da kai hari a New York City wanda ya kashe mutane takwas - hukuncin da ba a taba yi wa wani a jihar ba tun daga shekarar 1953.
Saipov, mai shekara 30, ana tuhumarsa da amfani da wata babbar motar haya da Home Depot ta yi amfani da ita wajen kai hari a kan hanyar da ke kan titin Western Highway a Lower Manhattan, inda ta ji wa masu tafiya da masu kekuna rauni a cikin watan Oktoba.
Don a ba da cikakken hukunci, masu gabatar da kara za su tabbatar da cewa Saipov ya kashe mutane takwas da gangan kuma ya haifar da mummunan rauni na jiki, bisa ga wata sanarwa da aka yi a Yankin Kudu na New York.
Kotunan biyu za su iya ba da hukunci mai tsanani, kamar yadda kotun ya rubuta.
Makonni bayan harin, wata kotun tarayya ta tuhumi Saipov da tuhumar da ta kai 22 da suka hada da tuhumar kisa takwas da ake yi don yaudara, tuhumar da ake yawan amfani da ita a shari'o'in aikata laifuka, da kuma tuhumar cin zarafi da lalata motoci.
Masu gabatar da kara sun ce harin ya bukaci dabaru da shiryawa sosai, suna bayyana harin Saipov a matsayin "mai saurin kai hari, mai zalunci da kuma lalata".
"Sayfullo Habibullaevic Saipov ya yi sanadin rauni, lalacewa da asarar rayuka ga iyalai da kuma abokan Diego Enrique Angelini, Nicholas Cleves, Ann-Laure Decadt, Darren Drake, Ariel Erlij, Hernan Ferruchi, Hernan Diego Mendoza, da Alejandro Damian Pagnucco", in ji wani gargadin da ake yi da gangan.
Biyar daga cikin wadanda aka kashe 'yan kasar Argentina ne.
Shekara goma ta wuce tun lokacin da New York's Eastern District ya gabatar da hukuncin kisa.
An yanke wa mai laifin, Khalid Barnes, hukuncin kisa a kan masu safarar miyagun kwayoyi biyu amma an yanke masa hukuncin rai da rai a watan Satumbar 2009.
A 1953 ne aka yanke hukuncin kisa mafi tsanani a New York a kan Julius da Ethel Rosenberg, ma'aurata da aka kashe bayan da aka yanke musu hukuncin kisa a kan aikata laifin leƙen asiri a madadin Soviet Union a lokacin yakin Cold War shekaru biyu da suka gabata.
Dukansu sun mutu a cikin kujera a ranar 19 ga Yuni, 1953.
Saipov, dan kasar Uzbekistan, bai nuna nadama ba a cikin kwanaki da watanni bayan harin, a cewar bayanan kotu.
'Yar ta gaya wa masu binciken cewa tana jin dadi sosai game da abin da ta yi,' in ji 'yan sanda.
Saipov ya shaida wa hukumomi cewa an yi wahayi zuwa gare shi don kai harin bayan kallon bidiyon ISIS a kan wayarsa, in ji rahoton.
Ya kuma nemi a saka masa tutar ISIS a cikin ɗakinsa a asibiti, in ji 'yan sanda.
Ya ce bai da laifi a kan tuhume-tuhum 22 da ake yi masa.
David Patton, daya daga cikin masu kare da ke wakiltar Saipov, ya ce ya yi matukar bakin ciki da hukuncin da kotun ta yanke.
"Mun yi imanin cewa yanke hukuncin neman a yi musu hukunci mafi tsanani maimakon a amince da laifin da aka yanke musu na ɗaurin rai da rai ba tare da yiwuwar samun 'yanci ba, zai kara jawo wa duk wanda abin ya shafa, ciwo na abubuwan da suka faru", in ji Patton.
Kungiyar kare Saipov ta riga ta nemi masu gabatar da kara da su daina neman hukunci mafi girma.
ASA Turkiyya ya ce Nigel FARAGE ya kamata a ke kula da Brexit tattaunawa
Nigel Farage ya yi alkawarin zai yi amfani da muryar jama'a a yau yayin wani zanga-zanga a taron na Dori.
Tsohon shugaban UKIP ya ce 'yan siyasa dole ne su ji matsin lamba daga 'yan EU - kamar yadda wani dan majalisar Theresa May da kansa ya nuna cewa ya kamata ya zama mai kula da tattaunawar da EU.
